Dear Sir/Madam,

SUBJECT ACCESS REQUEST UNDER UK GDPR ARTICLE 15 AND THE DATA PROTECTION ACT 2018

I am writing to make a subject access request for personal data held by the Metropolitan Police Service relating to me in connection with an incident at NatWest, Brixton Road on Tuesday 21 September 2021.


MY DETAILS

Full name:              Arthur Douglas Noel
Date of birth:          06 October 1977
Address:                500 Brixton Road, London SW9 8EQ
Duration at address:    Approximately 20 years continuous residence


THE INCIDENT

On Tuesday 21 September 2021 at approximately 08:59 UTC, I attended the NatWest branch on Brixton Road (adjacent to my home address) to withdraw cash from my own account using my passport as identification. I was refused service by the branch manager. I left the premises voluntarily. After I had left, NatWest staff called 999. Metropolitan Police officers attended my home address at 500 Brixton Road within approximately five minutes of the call.

No crime was committed. No threat was made. I had left the premises before the call was made. I have video evidence of the interaction inside the bank, recorded before I left.

Full background, video evidence, transcript, and stills are published at: https://github.com/roundtable-love/natwest


INFORMATION REQUESTED

I request disclosure of all personal data held about me in connection with this incident, including but not limited to:


1. THE 999 CALL

- The 999 call recording in its original digital format.
- The CAD (Computer Aided Dispatch) record for the call, including the time received, the caller's details, the nature of the call as recorded by the operator, the grading/priority assigned, and the dispatch time.
- Any transcript or summary of the call created by the operator or any other officer.


2. INCIDENT LOG AND CRIME REPORT

- The full incident log for this call.
- Any crime report, intelligence submission, or CRIMINT entry generated in connection with the incident.
- Any CRIS entry relating to the incident.
- The recorded outcome or disposal of the incident.


3. ATTENDING OFFICERS

- The names, shoulder numbers, and unit of the officers who attended my address.
- All body-worn video footage from attending officers.
- Any notes, pocket notebook entries, or statements made by attending officers in connection with the incident.
- Any record of what the attending officers were told before or upon arrival (i.e. the briefing or CAD update they received en route).


4. INTELLIGENCE AND MARKERS

- Any intelligence log, marker, flag, or nominal record created or updated in connection with this incident.
- Any risk assessment or threat marker associated with my name or address that was created or updated as a result of this incident.
- Any PNC or PND entry created or updated in connection with this incident.


5. COMMUNICATIONS WITH NATWEST

- All records of any communication between the Metropolitan Police and NatWest (including the Brixton Road branch) relating to this incident, including any follow-up after the initial attendance.


FORMAT

I request that all data be provided in electronic format where possible. For audio recordings, I request copies in their original digital format. For body-worn video, I request the original digital file.


LEGAL BASIS

This request is made under Article 15 of UK GDPR and Part 3, Chapter 3 of the Data Protection Act 2018 (law enforcement processing). I am aware that certain exemptions may apply under Schedule 2, Part 1 of the DPA 2018 but note that any exemption must be applied on a case-by-case basis and must be necessary and proportionate.


RESPONSE

You are required to respond within one calendar month of receipt of this request. If you require proof of identity, please advise immediately so that I can provide it without delay to the statutory deadline.

If any data is withheld, I require a written explanation of the specific exemption relied upon for each category of data withheld.


